frameDefinitions: The Subparts of Clothing items worn by a Wearer and made of a certain Material.
This frame is concerned with words that describe a person based on a salient part of their body.
Temporary or permanent Styles and Configurations of Hair, as well as its inherent Nature.
A Guest stays for a time at a Location, which is not his or her permanent residence, for some Duration.
This frame covers words for Body_part(s) (BP) belonging to a Possessor (Poss), which may be characterized by a Descriptor (Desc).
A Perceiver determines the Location of a Sought_entity within a Ground.
frameExamples: The shirt features a long <t>sleeve</t> with shiny gold buttons.
On either side her head gleamed coiled <t>braids</t> of dark-gold hair , almost pale copper in the subdued light of the room .
I usually <t>stay</t> with my aunt at her summer house when I go to Seville.
He had to brace his right <t><fex name='Body_part'>arm</fex></t> against his leg in order to fight the roll.
Kim <t>found</t> his hat on the far side.
listRoleDefinitions: This is a <fen>Subpart</fen> of the <fen>Clothing</fen> item.
This role identifies the <fen>Individual</fen> (or individuals) being described.
This role identifies the <fen>Figure</fen> or form being described by the target.
This role is the hair itself
This role is the Possessor of the body part.
Temporary Configurations of hair (eg braid, bun, ponytail).   Something done to the hair merely by movement.
A property of the hair (eg curly, fine, brown).  This acts much like 'Descriptor' in the Observable_bodyparts Frame.  Colors, styles, natural properties are described by this frame element.
The <fen>Guest</fen> remains for a relatively short period of time in the <fen>Location</fen>.
The <fen>Location</fen> where the <fen>Guest</fen> spends a short amount of time.
The length of time that the <fen>Guest</fen> remains at the <fen>Location</fen>.
The <fen>Host</fen> is living at the <fen>Location</fen> on a permanent basis, and is allowing the <fen>Guest</fen> to stay there.
The time at which the temporary stay takes place.
The <fen>Place</fen> indicates the larger physical setting of the temporary stay.
This Frame Element denotes the <fen>Possessor</fen> of the <fen>Body_part</fen>.
This Frame Element  is the <fen>Body_part</fen>.
The individual that determines the <fen>Location</fen> of the <fen>Sought_entity</fen>.
The entity that the <fen>Perceiver</fen> succeeds in finding.
The position of the <fen>Sought_entity</fen>.
The general set of entities that the <fen>Perceiver</fen> examined in order to find the <fen>Sought_entity</fen>.
The time when the <fen>Sought_entity</fen> is located.
listRoleExamples: The red-haired <fex>figure</fex> stood in the doorway.
Originally, <fex>we</fex> planned on rooming with our relatives in Reno.
Originally we planned on staying <fex>at the Hilton</fex>.
My wife and have just returned from a <fex>two day</fex> stay at Ocean Key.
You should avoid staying <fex>with old college buddies</fex> when on business trips.
<fex>In London</fex>, I stayed at a hotel.
<fex>I</fex> finally found the peanut underneath the couch cusion.
Sam located the Imperial regal <fex>among the coins in his pocket</fex> and passed it to the boy.
